# WebCouture 🌐

This website is built for a customer who wants to get more female customers to their company where they build and design websites.
The client has requested a website that appeals to the female clientele and asked for pink/purple colors
Welcome to **WebCouture** — a clean, responsive website designed to showcase professional web development services. Built with HTML, CSS, and a sprinkle of JavaScript, this site is optimized for both desktop and mobile, including iPhone 5 and up.

## 🚀 Live Site
🔗 [https://webbcouture.github.io/main/)

## 📁 Project Structure
├── index.html # Homepage ├── info.html # Info/About Page ├── contact.html # Contact form page ├── assets/ │ ├── images/ # All banner and content images │ ├── favicon/ # Icons and touch icons │ └── css/ │ └── styles.css # Main stylesheet

## 📱 Features
- 🔥 Modern & responsive layout
- 🎨 Stylish black, pink, and white color palette
- 📱 Mobile-first design (compatible with iPhone 5 and up)
- 🧠 Informational page explaining services
- 💬 Contact form with confirmation message
- 📸 Full-width image banners and icons via Font Awesome
- 🌐 Language set to English, with semantic tags and SEO meta tags

## 🖥 Pages Overview
### `index.html` - Home
- Banner section with marketing tagline
- Highlights the design and build services
- Uses Flexbox and background image styling

### `info.html` - Info
- Focuses on the company’s philosophy and experience
- Includes a smaller, aligned banner image
- Text styled with Georgia font for readability

### `contact.html` - Contact
- Stacked contact form with `name`, `email`, and `message`
- JavaScript form confirmation message
- Styled submit button and responsive layout

## 🧪 Testing
### Tested on:
- ✅ iPhone 5 (320px width)
- ✅ iPad (768px width)
- ✅ Desktop (1024px+)
- ✅ Chrome, Safari, Firefox

## Accessibility:
- Logical heading structure (`<h1>` to `<h3>`)
- Alt text for images
- Labels on all form fields
- Uses semantic HTML5 tags

## 📦 Built With
- HTML5
- CSS3 (Flexbox, media queries)
- JavaScript (for form interaction)
- Google Fonts (`Lato`, `Oswald`)
- Font Awesome for icons

## 📌 Future Improvements
- Add dark/light mode toggle 🌗
- Add backend functionality for form submissions 📬
- Include customer testimonials 🗣️
- Implement multilingual support 🌍

